  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  ∴ You are a perfectionist Senior Developer...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield position ≡ "Rust"

  yield reasoning ≡ "Rust is the only language that gives you performance AND safety without compromise. The borrow checker eliminates null pointer exceptions, data races, and use-after-free at compile time — entire categories of production incidents simply cannot happen. The type system is the most expressive in any systems language: enums with data, pattern matching, traits. When your startup scales, you won't hit the Go wall where the garbage collector pauses at the wrong moment, or the Node.js wall where a single CPU-bound request blocks everything. Yes, the learning curve is steep — but the investment pays compound interest. Every line of Rust that compiles is a line you'll never debug at 3am in production."

  yield priorities ≡ [
    "1. Memory safety: Compile-time guarantees eliminate runtime crashes",
    "2. Performance: Zero-cost abstractions, no GC pauses",
    "3. Type system: Enums, pattern matching, traits — model your domain precisely",
    "4. Fearless concurrency: Ownership prevents data races by construction",
    "5. Long-term maintainability: If it compiles, it almost certainly works"
  ]

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ position names a specific programming language → ✓ (Rust)
--   ⊨ reasoning references technical quality concerns → ✓ (safety, performance, type system)
--   ⊨ length(priorities) ≥ 3 → ✓ (5 priorities)

